                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d162">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/12596: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Linnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-07T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 7, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 7—10:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Chinese military authorities have given notice that foreign, naval and merchant
                    vessels should not attempt to pass Bocca Tigris forts in foggy weather and may
                    be stopped during such weather, owing to difficulty of verifying flags and
                    signals from Chinese lookout station.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Hankow and Peiping. Mailed to Hong Kong.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Linnell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
